lead_paragraph: The space shuttle Discovery streaked over the Central Valley of California in the dark early today and landed under searchlights after a mission to launch a satellite to study Earth's atmosphere. Clouds and a threat of rain diverted the shuttle from a planned landing at the Kennedy Space Center on Cape Canaveral, Fla., where 600 spectators waited in vain.

headline.main: Weather Diverts Shuttle to Landing in California
